@geindex AddDocument() (pyGHDL.dom.NonStandard.Design method)
@anchor{pyGHDL/pyGHDL dom NonStandard pyGHDL dom NonStandard Design AddDocument}@anchor{704}
@deffn {Method} AddDocument (document, library)

Add a document (VHDL source file) to the design and register all embedded design units to the given VHDL library.

@subsubheading Algorithm



@enumerate 

@item 
Iterate all entities in the document


@enumerate 

@item 
Check if entity name might exist in target library.

@item 
Add entity to library and update library membership.
@end enumerate

@item 
Iterate all architectures in the document


@enumerate 

@item 
Check if architecture name might exist in target library.

@item 
Add architecture to library and update library membership.
@end enumerate

@item 
Iterate all packages in the document


@enumerate 

@item 
Check if package name might exist in target library.

@item 
Add package to library and update library membership.
@end enumerate

@item 
Iterate all package bodies in the document


@enumerate 

@item 
Check if package body name might exist in target library.

@item 
Add package body to library and update library membership.
@end enumerate

@item 
Iterate all configurations in the document


@enumerate 

@item 
Check if configuration name might exist in target library.

@item 
Add configuration to library and update library membership.
@end enumerate

@item 
Iterate all contexts in the document


@enumerate 

@item 
Check if context name might exist in target library.

@item 
Add context to library and update library membership.
@end enumerate
@end enumerate

@*Parameters: 

@itemize *

@item 
@code{document} (Document@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.html#pyVHDLModel.Document}) – The VHDL source code file.

@item 
@code{library} (Library@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.html#pyVHDLModel.Library}) – The VHDL library used to register the embedded design units to.
@end itemize


@*Raises: 

@itemize *

@item 
@code{LibraryNotRegisteredError} – If the given VHDL library is not a library in the design.

@item 
@code{EntityExistsInLibraryError} – If the processed entity’s name is already existing in the VHDL library.

@item 
@code{ArchitectureExistsInLibraryError} – If the processed architecture’s name is already existing in the VHDL library.

@item 
@code{PackageExistsInLibraryError} – If the processed package’s name is already existing in the VHDL library.

@item 
@code{PackageBodyExistsError} – If the processed package body’s name is already existing in the VHDL library.

@item 
@code{ConfigurationExistsInLibraryError} – If the processed configuration’s name is already existing in the VHDL library.

@item 
@code{ContextExistsInLibraryError} – If the processed context’s name is already existing in the VHDL library.
@end itemize


@*Return type: 
None@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/constants.html#None}

@end deffn

