@geindex AnalyzeDependencies() (pyGHDL.dom.NonStandard.Design method)
@anchor{pyGHDL/pyGHDL dom NonStandard pyGHDL dom NonStandard Design AnalyzeDependencies}@anchor{702}
@deffn {Method} AnalyzeDependencies ()

Analyze the dependencies of design units.

@*Return type: 
None@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/constants.html#None}


@subsubheading Algorithm



@enumerate 

@item 
Create all vertices of the dependency graph by iterating all design units in all libraries. 
→ @ref{708,,CreateDependencyGraph()}

@item 
Create the compile order graph. 
→ @ref{709,,CreateCompileOrderGraph()}

@item 
Index all packages. 
→ @ref{70a,,IndexPackages()}

@item 
Index all architectures. 
→ @ref{70b,,IndexArchitectures()}

@item 
Link all contexts 
→ @ref{70c,,LinkContexts()}

@item 
Link all architectures. 
→ @ref{70d,,LinkArchitectures()}

@item 
Link all package bodies. 
→ @ref{70e,,LinkPackageBodies()}

@item 
Link all library references. 
→ @code{LinkLibraryReferences()}

@item 
Link all package references. 
→ @code{LinkPackageReferences()}

@item 
Link all context references. 
→ @code{LinkContextReferences()}

@item 
Link all components. 
→ @code{LinkComponents()}

@item 
Link all instantiations. 
→ @code{LinkInstantiations()}

@item 
Create the hierarchy graph. 
→ @ref{70f,,CreateHierarchyGraph()}

@item 
Compute the compile order. 
→ @code{ComputeCompileOrder()}
@end enumerate
@end deffn

