@deffn {Method} CreateCompileOrderGraph ()

Create a compile-order graph with bidirectional references to the dependency graph.

Add vertices representing a document (VHDL source file) to the dependency graph. Each “document” vertex in dependency graph is copied into the compile-order
graph and bidirectionally referenced.

In addition, each vertex of a corresponding design unit in a document is linked to the vertex representing that document to express the design unit in
document relationship.

Each added vertex has the following properties:


@itemize *

@item 
The vertex’ ID is the document’s filename.

@item 
The vertex’ value references the document.

@item 
A key-value-pair called @code{kind} denotes the vertex’s kind as an enumeration value of type @code{DependencyGraphVertexKind}.

@item 
A key-value-pair called @code{predefined} does not exist.
@end itemize

@subsubheading Algorithm



@enumerate 

@item 
Iterate all documents in the design.


@itemize *

@item 
Create a vertex for that document and reference the document by the vertex’ value field. 
In return, set the documents’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.html#pyVHDLModel.Document._dependencyVertex} field to reference the created vertex.

@item 
Copy the vertex from dependency graph to compile-order graph and link both vertices bidirectionally. 
In addition, set the documents’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.html#pyVHDLModel.Document._dependencyVertex} field to reference the copied vertex.


@itemize *

@item 
Add a key-value-pair called @code{compileOrderVertex} to the dependency graph’s vertex.

@item 
Add a key-value-pair called @code{dependencyVertex} to the compiler-order graph’s vertex.
@end itemize
@end itemize


@enumerate 

@item 
Iterate the documents design units and create an edge from the design unit’s corresponding dependency vertex to the documents corresponding
dependency vertex. This expresses a “design unit is located in document” relation.


@itemize *

@item 
Add a key-value-pair called @cite{kind`} denoting the edge’s kind as an enumeration value of type @code{DependencyGraphEdgeKind}.
@end itemize
@end enumerate
@end enumerate

@*Return type: 
None@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/constants.html#None}

@end deffn

@geindex CreateDependencyGraph() (pyGHDL.dom.NonStandard.Design method)
@anchor{pyGHDL/pyGHDL dom NonStandard pyGHDL dom NonStandard Design CreateDependencyGraph}@anchor{708}
@deffn {Method} CreateDependencyGraph ()

Create all vertices of the dependency graph by iterating all design units in all libraries.

This method will purely create a sea of vertices without any linking between vertices. The edges will be created later by other methods. 
See @ref{702,,AnalyzeDependencies()} for these methods and their algorithmic order.

Each vertex has the following properties:


@itemize *

@item 
The vertex’ ID is the design unit’s identifier.

@item 
The vertex’ value references the design unit.

@item 
A key-value-pair called @code{kind} denotes the vertex’s kind as an enumeration value of type @code{DependencyGraphVertexKind}.

@item 
A key-value-pair called @code{predefined} denotes if the referenced design unit is a predefined language entity.
@end itemize

@subsubheading Algorithm



@enumerate 

@item 
Iterate all libraries in the design.


@itemize *

@item 
Create a vertex for that library and reference the library by the vertex’ value field. 
In return, set the library’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.html#pyVHDLModel.Library._dependencyVertex} field to reference the created vertex.
@end itemize


@enumerate 

@item 
Iterate all contexts in that library.


@itemize *

@item 
Create a vertex for that context and reference the context by the vertex’ value field. 
In return, set the context’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.html#pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.Context._dependencyVertex} field to reference the created vertex.
@end itemize

@item 
Iterate all packages in that library.


@itemize *

@item 
Create a vertex for that package and reference the package by the vertex’ value field. 
In return, set the package’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.html#pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.Package._dependencyVertex} field to reference the created vertex.
@end itemize

@item 
Iterate all package bodies in that library.


@itemize *

@item 
Create a vertex for that package body and reference the package body by the vertex’ value field. 
In return, set the package body’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.html#pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.PackageBody._dependencyVertex} field to reference the created vertex.
@end itemize

@item 
Iterate all entities in that library.


@itemize *

@item 
Create a vertex for that entity and reference the entity by the vertex’ value field. 
In return, set the entity’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.html#pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.Entity._dependencyVertex} field to reference the created vertex.
@end itemize

@item 
Iterate all architectures in that library.


@itemize *

@item 
Create a vertex for that architecture and reference the architecture by the vertex’ value field. 
In return, set the architecture’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.html#pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.Architecture._dependencyVertex} field to reference the created vertex.
@end itemize

@item 
Iterate all configurations in that library.


@itemize *

@item 
Create a vertex for that configuration and reference the configuration by the vertex’ value field. 
In return, set the configuration’s _dependencyVertex@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.html#pyVHDLModel.DesignUnit.Configuration._dependencyVertex} field to reference the created vertex.
@end itemize
@end enumerate
@end enumerate

@*Return type: 
None@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/constants.html#None}

@end deffn

