@geindex GetName() (in module pyGHDL.dom._Translate)
@anchor{pyGHDL/pyGHDL dom _Translate pyGHDL dom _Translate GetName}@anchor{a40}
@deffn {Function} pyGHDL.dom._Translate.GetName (node)

Translates a `name' IIR node to a Name@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.Name.html#pyVHDLModel.Name.Name}.

A name can be a `simple name' or complex name consisting of `selected', `parenthesis', `attribute', … `names'.
Complex names are composed as a chain of name objects, which can be traversed using the
Prefix@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.Name.html#pyVHDLModel.Name.Name.Prefix} property.

@*Parameters: 
@code{node} (TypeVar@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#typing.TypeVar}(@code{Iir}, bound= c_int@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/ctypes.html#ctypes.c_int})) – The name IIR node to translate.


@*Return type: 
Name@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.Name.html#pyVHDLModel.Name.Name}


@*Returns: 
A name object.

@end deffn

