@deffn {Function} pyGHDL.dom._Translate.GetSubtypeIndicationFromNode (node, entity, name)

Extracts the subtype indication from an IIR node and translates it to a Symbol@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.Symbol.html#pyVHDLModel.Symbol.Symbol}.

@cartouche
@quotation Note 
This function calls @ref{a45,,GetSubtypeIndicationFromIndicationNode()}.

This function should be used directly if @code{nodes.Get_Subtype_Indication(...)} was already called or a
subtype indication is return by another getter.
@end quotation
@end cartouche

@*Parameters: 

@itemize *

@item 
@code{node} (TypeVar@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#typing.TypeVar}(@code{Iir}, bound= c_int@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/ctypes.html#ctypes.c_int})) – The IIR node to get the subtype indication from.

@item 
@code{entity} (str@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str}) – The entity kind the subtype indication is extracted from (e.g. @code{constant}). Used in exception messages.

@item 
@code{name} (str@footnote{https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str}) – The entity’s name the subtype indication is extracted from (e.g. @code{BITS}). Used in exception messages.
@end itemize


@*Return type: 
Symbol@footnote{https://vhdl.github.io/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel/pyVHDLModel.Symbol.html#pyVHDLModel.Symbol.Symbol}


@*Returns: 
A symbol representing a reference to a type/subtype and possible array or record constraints.

@end deffn

