@geindex to_bytes() (pyGHDL.libghdl.vhdl.nodes.Iir_Kind method)
@anchor{pyGHDL/pyGHDL libghdl vhdl nodes pyGHDL libghdl vhdl nodes Iir_Kind to_bytes}@anchor{fa7}
@deffn {Method} to_bytes (length=1, byteorder='big', *, signed=False)

Return an array of bytes representing an integer.


@table @asis

@item length

Length of bytes object to use.  An OverflowError is raised if the
integer is not representable with the given number of bytes.  Default
is length 1.

@item byteorder

The byte order used to represent the integer.  If byteorder is ‘big’,
the most significant byte is at the beginning of the byte array.  If
byteorder is ‘little’, the most significant byte is at the end of the
byte array.  To request the native byte order of the host system, use
>>`<<sys.byteorder’ as the byte order value.  Default is to use ‘big’.

@item signed

Determines whether two’s complement is used to represent the integer.
If signed is False and a negative integer is given, an OverflowError
is raised.
@end table
@end deffn

@geindex from_bytes() (pyGHDL.libghdl.vhdl.nodes.Iir_Kind class method)
@anchor{pyGHDL/pyGHDL libghdl vhdl nodes pyGHDL libghdl vhdl nodes Iir_Kind from_bytes}@anchor{fa8}
@deffn {Method} classmethod from_bytes (bytes, byteorder='big', *, signed=False)

Return the integer represented by the given array of bytes.


@table @asis

@item bytes

Holds the array of bytes to convert.  The argument must either
support the buffer protocol or be an iterable object producing bytes.
Bytes and bytearray are examples of built-in objects that support the
buffer protocol.

@item byteorder

The byte order used to represent the integer.  If byteorder is ‘big’,
the most significant byte is at the beginning of the byte array.  If
byteorder is ‘little’, the most significant byte is at the end of the
byte array.  To request the native byte order of the host system, use
>>`<<sys.byteorder’ as the byte order value.  Default is to use ‘big’.

@item signed

Indicates whether two’s complement is used to represent the integer.
@end table
@end deffn

@geindex as_integer_ratio() (pyGHDL.libghdl.vhdl.nodes.Iir_Kind method)
@anchor{pyGHDL/pyGHDL libghdl vhdl nodes pyGHDL libghdl vhdl nodes Iir_Kind as_integer_ratio}@anchor{fa9}
@deffn {Method} as_integer_ratio ()

Return a pair of integers, whose ratio is equal to the original int.

The ratio is in lowest terms and has a positive denominator.

@example
>>> (10).as_integer_ratio()
(10, 1)
>>> (-10).as_integer_ratio()
(-10, 1)
>>> (0).as_integer_ratio()
(0, 1)
@end example
@end deffn

